{{Dicdef|date=July 2018}} '''Amanah''' ({{lang-ar|أمانة}}) is an [[Arabic]] term used for [[mayor|mayoralty]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=gthHAAAAYAAJ&q=amanat+mayoralty&dq=amanat+mayoralty&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjY5ofpq4TXAhVBYVAKHVdSCskQ6AEILjAB|title=MEED.|last=|first=|date=1971|publisher=Economic East Economic Digest, Limited|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=538|language=en}}</ref> or [[municipality]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=MZ5pCwAAQBAJ&pg=PA414&dq=amanah+municipality&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjg4bPSq4TXAhUNblAKHVCQBq8Q6AEIKDAA#v=onepage&q=amanah%20municipality&f=false|title=Human Settlement Development - Volume IV|last=Sassen|first=Saskia|date=2009-09-30|publisher=EOLSS Publications|year=|isbn=9781848260474|location=|pages=414|language=en}}</ref>
In some [[Arabic countries]], the Amanah is the municipality of the capital.
== Examples == * [[Mayoralty of Baghdad|Amanat Baghdad]] ({{lang|ar|أمانة بغداد}}) * [[Greater Amman Municipality]] ({{lang|ar|أمانة عمان الكبرى}}) * [[Municipality of the Holy City]] ({{lang|ar|أمانة العصمة المقدسة}}) * [[Sana Municipality]] ({{lang|ar|أمانة العاصمة}})
