{{climate chart | [[Valencia]] | 7.7 | 16.7 | 36 | 7.9 | 17.2 | 32 | 9.8 | 19.7 | 35 | 11.8 | 21.2 | 37 | 15.1 | 23.8 | 34 | 18.9 | 28.2 | 23 | 21.8 | 30.1 | 9 | 22.4 | 30.6 | 19 | 18.6 | 27.6 | 51 | 15.5 | 24.6 | 74 | 10.5 | 19.6 | 51 | 8.1 | 16.8 | 52 |float=right |source=[[World Meteorological Organization|WMO]]<ref name="WMO">{{cite web |url=http://www.worldweather.org/083/c01238.htm |title=Weather Information for Valencia |accessdate=}}</ref>}}
[[Valencia]] and its metropolitan area have a hot-summer [[Mediterranean climate]] ([[Köppen climate classification]]: ''Csa'')<ref name=KGcc>{{Cite journal|author=M. Kottek|author2=J. Grieser |author3=C. Beck |author4=B. Rudolf |author5=F. Rubel |title=World Map of the Köppen-Geiger climate classification updated|journal=Meteorol. Z.|volume=15|pages=259–263|url=http://koeppen-geiger.vu-wien.ac.at/pics/kottek_et_al_2006.gif|doi=10.1127/0941-2948/2006/0130|accessdate=22 April 2009|year=2006|bibcode = 2006MetZe..15..259K }}</ref> with very mild winters and long warm to hot summers. According to Troll-Paffen climate classification, Valencia has a ''warm-temperate subtropical'' climate (''Warmgemäßigt-subtropisches Zonenklima'')<ref>[http://web.tiscali.it/linnets/Troll-Paffen.jpg Climatic map by Istituto Geografico De Agostini, according to Troll-Paffen climate classification] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121004052732/http://web.tiscali.it/linnets/Troll-Paffen.jpg |date=October 4, 2012 }}</ref> and according to Siegmund/Frankenberg climate classification, Valencia has subtropical climate.<ref>[http://www.ph-heidelberg.de/geographie/forschung-und-entwicklung/klimakarte-der-erde.html ''Die Klimatypen der Erde''] - Pädagogische Hochschule in [[Heidelberg]]</ref>
== Temperature ==
=== General === {| class="infobox bordered" style="text-align:center" |- !Yearly max temp !Yearly mean temp !Yearly min temp |- class="mergedrow" |{{convert|23.0|°C|°F|abbr=on}} |{{convert|18.4|°C|°F|abbr=on}} |{{convert|13.8|°C|°F|abbr=on}} |} Its average annual temperature is {{convert|23.0|°C|°F|abbr=on}} during the day and {{convert|13.8|°C|°F|abbr=on}} at night. In the coldest month – January, typically the temperature ranges from {{convert|14|to|20|C|F}} during the day and {{convert|4|to|12|C|F}} at night. In the warmest month – August, the typically temperature ranges from {{convert|28|to|34|C|F}} during the day and about {{convert|22|°C|°F|abbr=on}} at night. Large fluctuations in temperature are rare.<ref name="AEMET" />
=== Seasonal climate === [[File:Puente de las flores.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Winter in Valencia: very mild temperatures and mostly green flora.]]
==== Winter ==== Winters in Valencia are very mild. December, January and February are the coldest months, with average temperatures around {{convert|17|°C|°F|abbr=on}} during the day and {{convert|8|°C|°F|abbr=on}} at night. From a few to a dozen days in the winter, the temperature exceeds {{convert|20|°C|°F|abbr=on}}. Because of the very mild temperatures in winter, most of the vegetation remains green throughout the year.
March is a transitional month, the temperature often exceeding {{convert|20|°C|0|abbr=on}}, with average temperature of around {{convert|20|°C|°F|abbr=on}} during the day and {{convert|10|°C|°F|abbr=on}} at night.<ref name="AEMET" />
==== Summer ==== Summers in Valencia area are long and warm to hot (in the middle of summer). Generally the summer season lasts about eight months, from April to November. Regular temperatures above {{convert|20|°C|°F|abbr=on}} begin as early as April, although in this month the sea temperature is still cool: about {{convert|15|-|16|C|F}}. The summer season ends in November, in this month sometimes occurring days with temperatures below {{convert|20|°C|°F|abbr=on}}. The sea temperature in November remains mild - about {{convert|18|°C|°F|abbr=on}}.
July and August are the warmest months, with average temperatures around {{convert|29|°C|°F|abbr=on}} during the day and {{convert|22|°C|°F|abbr=on}} at night. In June and September the average temperature is around {{convert|26|-|28|C|F}} during the day and {{convert|18|-|20|C|F}} at night. In May and October the average temperature is around {{convert|24|°C|°F|abbr=on}} during the day and {{convert|15|-|16|°C|°F|abbr=on}} at night and in April and November the average temperature is around {{convert|20|-|21|°C|°F|abbr=on}} during the day and {{convert|12|°C|°F|abbr=on}} at night.<ref name="AEMET" />
== Sunshine == [[Sunshine duration]] is 2,660 hours per year, from 150 - average about 5 hours of sunshine a day in December to 314 - average above 10 hours of sunshine a day in July.<ref name="AEMET">{{cite web |url=http://www.aemet.es/en/serviciosclimaticos/datosclimatologicos/valoresclimatologicos?l=8416&k=val |title=Standard Climate Values. Valencia}}</ref> This is a bit above average for the southern half of Europe because in this part of the continent, sunshine duration varies from about 2,000 to about 3,000 hours per year. However, this is a 70% larger value than in the northern half of Europe, where sunshine duration is around 1500 hours per year.{{citation needed|date=May 2016}} In winter Valencia has about three times more sun duration than in the northern half of Europe.{{citation needed|date=May 2016}}
