== Precipitation == Valencia has on average only 44 precipitation days a year, averaging several rainy days per month (≥ 1&nbsp;mm), ranging from 1 in July to 6 in October. The average annual precipitation is less than 454&nbsp;mm (17.87 inches), ranging from 9&nbsp;mm (0.35 inch) in July to 74&nbsp;mm (2.91 inch) in October.<ref name="AEMET" />
{{Weather box |location= Valencia <small>(precipitation days – 1&nbsp;mm)</small> |metric first= yes |single line= yes |Jan precipitation mm= 36 |Feb precipitation mm= 32 |Mar precipitation mm= 35 |Apr precipitation mm= 37 |May precipitation mm= 34 |Jun precipitation mm= 23 |Jul precipitation mm= 9 |Aug precipitation mm= 19 |Sep precipitation mm= 51 |Oct precipitation mm= 74 |Nov precipitation mm= 51 |Dec precipitation mm= 52 |year precipitation mm= 454 |Jan precipitation days= 4 |Feb precipitation days= 3 |Mar precipitation days= 4 |Apr precipitation days= 5 |May precipitation days= 5 |Jun precipitation days= 3 |Jul precipitation days= 1 |Aug precipitation days= 2 |Sep precipitation days= 4 |Oct precipitation days= 5 |Nov precipitation days= 4 |Dec precipitation days= 5 |year precipitation days= 44 |unit precipitation days= 1&nbsp;mm |source 1= [[Agencia Estatal de Meteorología]]<ref name="AEMET" /> |date=May 2013}} {{Weather box |location = Valencia <small>(precipitation days – 0.1&nbsp;mm)</small> |metric first = yes |single line = yes |Jan precipitation days = 6 |Feb precipitation days = 6 |Mar precipitation days = 6 |Apr precipitation days = 7 |May precipitation days = 8 |Jun precipitation days = 5 |Jul precipitation days = 2 |Aug precipitation days = 4 |Sep precipitation days = 6 |Oct precipitation days = 7 |Nov precipitation days = 6 |Dec precipitation days = 7 |year precipitation days = |unit precipitation days = 0.1&nbsp;mm |source 1 = [[World Meteorological Organization]]<ref name="WMO"/> |date=September 2014}}
== Humidity == Average [[relative humidity]] is 65%, ranging from 60% in April to 68% in August.<ref name="AEMET" />
{{Weather box |location = Valencia |metric first = yes |single line = yes |Jan humidity = 63 |Feb humidity = 61 |Mar humidity = 61 |Apr humidity = 60 |May humidity = 65 |Jun humidity = 65 |Jul humidity = 66 |Aug humidity = 68 |Sep humidity = 67 |Oct humidity = 66 |Nov humidity = 65 |Dec humidity = 65 |year humidity = 65 |source 1 = [[Agencia Estatal de Meteorología]]<ref name="AEMET" /> |date=May 2013}}
== Daylight == Valencia enjoys one of the most optimal number of hours of daylight in Europe. Days in winter are not as short as in the northern part of the continent. The average hours of daylight in December, January and February is 10 hours<ref name=weather2travel /> (for comparison: [[London]]<ref>http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/united-kingdom/london.php</ref> or [[Moscow]]<ref>http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/russia-europe/moscow.php</ref> or [[Warsaw]]<ref>http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/poland/warsaw.php</ref> - about 8 hours). {| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center;" |+Average hours of daylight<ref name=weather2travel /> |- ! Hours ! Jan ! Feb ! Mar ! Apr ! May ! Jun ! Jul ! Aug ! Sep ! Oct ! Nov ! Dec |- ! Day | 10 | 11 | 12 | 13 | 15 | 15 | 15 | 14 | 13 | 12 | 11 | 10 |- ! Twilight/Night | 14 | 13 | 12 | 11 | 9 | 9 | 9 | 10 | 11 | 12 | 13 | 14 |}
