== Curio == Valencia has a similar [[latitude]] to [[Madrid]]. However, the climate of these Spanish cities is very different, as Valencia is located at the seaside; Madrid is located in the approximate middle of the inland plateau. Valencia has much warmer winters (data from January, the coldest month): *Valencia: {{convert|16.4|°C|°F|abbr=on}} during the day and {{convert|7.1|°C|°F|abbr=on}} at night *Madrid: {{convert|10|°C|°F|abbr=on}} during the day and {{convert|2|°C|°F|abbr=on}} at night<ref>[http://www.aemet.es/en/serviciosclimaticos/datosclimatologicos/valoresclimatologicos?l=3195&k=mad Standard Climate Values. Madrid] - Agencia Estatal de Meteorología</ref> and also Valencia has longer summers and milder temperatures in the middle of summer during the day.
