'''San Roque''' is a settlement in [[Saipan]], in the [[Northern Mariana Islands]]. It is located to the north of [[Tanapag]] on the island's northwest coast, close to the point where the [[barrier reef]] protecting the [[Tanapag Harbor]] joins to the island. It is connected to Tanapag by the Marpi Road ([[Northern Mariana Islands Highway 30|Highway 30]]), which runs the length of the northwestern coast.

==Education==
[[Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands Public School System]] operates local public schools. Gregorio T. Camacho Elementary School is located in San Roque.<ref>"[https://web.archive.org/web/20080224102742/http://www.pss.cnmi.mp/PSSCentralOffice/index.cfm?pageID=2 CNMI PUBLIC SCHOOLS]." [[Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands Public School System]]. February 24, 2008. Retrieved on January 1, 2018.</ref> It opened as the San Roque Elementary School in 1951 and was renamed after the first commissioner of San Roque, Gregorio T. Camacho. Camacho served as the president of the school's [[parent-teacher association]].<ref>Santos, Amanda (6th grade student in the 1994-1995 school year). "[https://web.archive.org/web/20070828132946/http://www.pss.cnmi.mp/GTCamacho/index.cfm?pageID=5 HISTORY OF GTC ELEMENTARY SCHOOL]." Gregorio T. Camacho Elementary School. August 28, 2007. Retrieved on January 15, 2018.</ref>

