[[Image:Shaman-Gora.jpg|thumb|Shaman-Gora in the summer]]

'''Shaman-Gora''' ({{lang-ru|Шаман-Гора}}) is an archeological site on the outskirts of the village of [[Duty (village)|Duty]] in [[Khiloksky District]] of [[Zabaykalsky Krai]]. It is famous for its about 100 [[petroglyph]]s dating from 4000–1000 BCE. It is thought to be a ritual site for the local tribes. There are two main strata and their [[Artifact (archaeology)|artifacts]] show that there was a highly developed society in the region at the [[confluence (geography)|confluence]] of the Duty River and Arey Rivers.

