'''Sinapalo''' or '''Sinapalu''' is a village on the island of [[Rota (island)|Rota]] in the [[Northern Mariana Islands]]. The village is the largest settlement on the island <ref>https://www.citypopulation.de/php/northmarianas-admin.php</ref> (followed by [[Songsong]], in the southwest), it is located south of the island's airport, [[Rota International Airport]], close to the centre of the island.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://travelingluck.com/Oceana/Northern%20Mariana%20Islands/general/_4041576_Sinapalo.html#local_map |title=Sinapalo / Sinapalo, general, Northern Mariana Islands, Oceania |location=MP |website=Travelingluck.com |date= |accessdate=2016-04-09}}</ref>
{{coord|14.1656|145.2308|scale:50000_region:US-MP|display=title}}

==Education==
[[Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands Public School System]]
* Sinapalo Elementary School is in Sinapalo<ref>https://www.cnmipss.org/school/sinapalo-elementary-school/</ref>
** Previously Rota Elementary & Junior High School in Songsong had elementary classes.<ref>"[https://web.archive.org/web/20070714212826/http://www.pss.cnmi.mp/RotaJuniorHigh/index.cfm?pageID=12 History & Background]." Rota Jr. High School. August 14, 2007. Retrieved on January 15, 2018.</ref> Sinapalo Elementary was built in two phases, with the Rota government and Rota Resort Hotel financing it. In 1995 phase I was built. There was a four-year hiatus in the construction that ended when the Rota government allowed it to continue. The school opened in February 2002 when phase II was built.<ref>"[https://web.archive.org/web/20070827042814/http://www.pss.cnmi.mp/Sinapalo/index.cfm?pageID=23 HISTORY]." Sinapalo Elementary School. August 27, 2007. Retrieved on January 15, 2018.</ref>
