{{Unreferenced|date=April 2014}} {{Infobox Valley |name =Valsesia | other_name = |photo = AltaValsesia0001.jpg |photo_caption = The upper Valsesia |coordinates = |location =[[Province of Vercelli|Vercelli]], [[Italy]] |orientation = NW - SW |length = |elevation = {{convert|300|-|4.554|m|abbr=on}} |type =[[River valley]] |map_image = Valsesiaposizione it.png |map_caption =Location of the valley in Piedmont, NW [[Italy]] }} [[File:Pan quarona dal tovo.jpg|thumb|Quarona from Monte Tovo]] '''Valsesia''' ({{lang-pms|Valsesia}}; [[Walser German]]: ''Tseschrutol''; {{lang-it|Valle della Sesia}}) is a group of valleys in the north-east of [[Piedmont]] in the [[Province of Vercelli]], [[Italy]]; the principal valley is that of the river [[Sesia]].
The major towns located here are [[Varallo Sesia]], [[Borgosesia]] and [[Serravalle Sesia]]; tourist villages include [[Alagna Valsesia]], [[Rima San Giuseppe]], [[Carcoforo]] and [[Scopello]]. While the valley mainly belongs to the [[province of Vercelli]] three of its ''[[comune|comuni]]'', namely [[Romagnano Sesia]], [[Prato Sesia]] and [[Grignasco]], are part of the [[province of Novara]].
==Summits== Summits that surround the valley include:
* [[Signalkuppe|Punta Gnifetti]] - 4,554 m * [[Parrotspitze|Punta Parrot]] - 4,432 m * [[Ludwigshöhe (mountain)|Ludwigshöhe]] - 4,342 m * [[Schwarzhorn (Monte Rosa Massif)|Corno Nero]] - 4,322 m * [[Corno Bianco]] - 3,320 m * [[Monte Tagliaferro]] - 2,964 m
