[[French Polynesia]] requires its residents to register their [[motor vehicle]]s and display '''[[vehicle registration plate]]s'''.<ref>http://www.worldlicenseplates.com/world/PA_POLY.html</ref> Current plates are [[Vehicle_registration_plates_of_Europe#Format|European standard]] 520 mm × 110 mm, and use French stamping dies. The [[overseas France|overseas departments and territories of France]] have three-digit codes, starting with 97, which was originally the single code for them all.<ref>http://www.plateshack.com/y2k/France2/france2y2k.html</ref> {|class="wikitable" |- !Image !First issued !Design !Slogan !Serial format !Serials issued !Notes |- |[[File:French Polynesia license plate 1993 series rear.png|150px]] |1993 | | | | | |- |[[File:French Polynesia license plate graphic.png|150px]] | | | | | | |- |}
